  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "Synthetic V&V 40 credibility evidence package for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The package embeds weakener W-AR-05: the primary validation result for the Output Comparison factor references a well-documented experimental dataset (Bludszuweit shear-stress hemolysis correlation, steady laminar pipe flow at 37 °C) whose operating regime overlaps the VAD COU on fluid properties, hematocrit, and shear-stress magnitude, but differs critically on flow unsteadiness — the comparator was acquired under steady laminar conditions, whereas the VAD COU requires prediction of hemolysis under pulsatile, turbulent-dominated impeller flow. The validation narrative presents the Bludszuweit dataset in strongly positive terms without examining this regime mismatch. The structural trigger is that the primary validation result object omits the comparedAgainst link entirely; a secondary result includes comparedAgainst to a predicate-device dataset to provide plausible cover.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-absolute-threshold",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-predicts-absolute-hemolyis-vad-cou2",
